HTML Notes
---

tag - <p> <html> <body> etc
content - between the tags
element - content plus tags
	empty element: has no content e.g. <img src='image/path' alt='whatever'>
attribute - 'options' in tag <p class="editor-note">
	class: attribute name
	editor-note: attribute value
		-serves as a label for later function

SECTIONS
<!DOCTYPE html> archaic but necessary
<html> wraps whole file
<head> contains everything that's not content; settings, keywords, search result blurb, CSS, etc
<body> contains content
<title> name appears on browser tab

<ul> unordered list
<ol> ordered list
	<li> tag that should surround each list element

<a href='link text'> link (a short for anchor, href short for hypertext reference)
